2267	\begin{proof}
2268	  \uses{lem:qcoh_section_localization_basicOpen, lem:mathlib_flat_of_isLocalized_span}
2269	  By the section-localization datum \cref{lem:qcoh_section_localization_basicOpen}, for each
2270	  \(g \in t\) the restriction \(\Gamma(\F, W) \to \Gamma(\F, D(g))\) exhibits
2271	  \(\Gamma(\F, D(g))\) as the away-localization \((\mathrm{powers}\,g)^{-1}\,\Gamma(\F, W)\)
2272	  of the source module at \(g\). The family \(t\) spans the unit ideal of the source ring
2273	  \(\Gamma(X, W)\), and each localized piece \(\Gamma(\F, D(g))\) is flat over the base
2274	  \(\Gamma(S, U)\) by hypothesis. The source-span flatness criterion
2275	  \cref{lem:mathlib_flat_of_isLocalized_span}, applied with base \(\Gamma(S, U)\), source
2276	  \(\Gamma(X, W)\), and these principal localizations, yields that \(\Gamma(\F, W)\) is flat
2277	  over \(\Gamma(S, U)\).
2278	\end{proof}
